Author-Name:  Wolpin, Kenneth I
Title:   The Career Decisions of Young Men. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 473-522
Issue: 3
Volume: 105
Year: 1997
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  This paper provides structural estimates of a dynamic model of schooling,
 work, and occupational choice decisions based on eleven years of
 observations on a sample of young men from the 1979 youth cohort of the
 National Longitudinal Surveys of Labor Market Experience (NLSY). The
 authors find that a suitably extended human capital investment model can
 in fact do an excellent job of fitting observed data on school attendance,
 work, occupational choices, and wages in the NLSY data on young men and
 also produces reasonable forecasts of future work decisions and wage
 patterns.   Copyright 1997 by the University of Chicago.
