Author-Name:    Cummings, Ronald G, et al
Title:   Are Hypothetical Referenda Incentive Compatible? 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 609-21
Issue: 3
Volume: 105
Year: 1997
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  Hypothetical referenda have been proposed as an incentive-compatible
 mechanism that can be used to obtain social valuations of environmental
 resources. The authors employ experimental methods to test the hypothesis
 that such referenda are indeed incentive compatible. Their results lead
 them to reject that hypothesis. Coauthors are Steven Elliott, Glenn W.
 Harrison, and James Murphy.   Copyright 1997 by the University of Chicago.
